WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.520
Dominoes. Quick starter. The First Flying Man. by Elspeth Roestron.

00:08.960 --> 00:15.200
Red by Ben Elliott, Wayne Forrester, Roger May, and Christopher Mills.

00:16.720 --> 00:20.480
Published and copyright Oxford University Press 2012.

00:30.000 --> 00:53.280
My story begins in the 1630s. It is the time of the Ottoman Empire.

00:53.520 --> 01:01.920
Hazarfen Ahmed Chalebi is a clever young man of those days.

01:03.920 --> 01:09.600
He lives in the district of Ushkudar in Istanbul.

01:11.600 --> 01:22.960
Every morning Hazarfen sits near the Bosphorus Strait. He looks at the tall tower in the district

01:22.960 --> 01:32.240
of Galota across the water. The Galota tower is taller than all the buildings near it.

01:35.200 --> 01:47.520
Simit! Would you like a simit? A man near Hazarfen calls. He has some tasty Turkish bread

01:47.520 --> 01:52.960
rings on his head. But Hazarfen doesn't answer.

01:55.520 --> 02:01.360
Every morning the man cries. Would you like a simit?

02:02.240 --> 02:14.000
But Hazarfen never answers. He doesn't hear or see the man. He is dreaming.

02:14.880 --> 02:22.480
In his dream, he is flying over the Bosphorus with the seabirds.

02:23.680 --> 02:29.680
One day I want to look down from the sky on Istanbul.

02:30.320 --> 02:38.160
He thinks. I want to fly across the strait with you, birds. But how?

02:44.880 --> 02:46.880
You

02:54.240 --> 02:59.920
Chapter 2 Drawings from Italy

03:14.640 --> 03:21.360
Weeks later, Hazarfen is near the Bosphorus again.

03:22.880 --> 03:27.760
Again he is looking carefully up at the seabirds in the sky.

03:29.760 --> 03:38.720
These days he is making some big wings in his workshop. He needs some help with the design.

03:39.520 --> 03:49.600
Hazarfen! Someone calls. Hazarfen sees his friend, Mehmed, with a second man.

03:51.120 --> 03:54.720
He goes over and says hello to the two of them.

03:56.000 --> 04:05.920
Hazarfen, this is my brother Ali. Mehmed says, he's got some drawings for you from Italy.

04:06.880 --> 04:15.440
They are old drawings of birds' wings by Leonardo da Vinci, Ali says.

04:16.320 --> 04:22.640
Ah yes, I know Leonardo's work. Hazarfen says.

04:23.680 --> 04:25.120
Let's see them then.

04:26.720 --> 04:32.720
Ali gives the drawings to Hazarfen. He looks at them for a minute.

04:33.600 --> 04:39.840
Interesting, Hazarfen says. Then he gives them back.

04:41.040 --> 04:42.480
Thank you Ali.

04:45.600 --> 04:52.560
Days later, in Hazarfen's workshop, my wings are ready.

04:53.520 --> 04:59.920
Hazarfen tells his friends. Let's see you fly then.

05:00.240 --> 05:02.880
You fly then, Mehmed cries.

05:03.760 --> 05:08.800
Your brother, Lagari wants to fly too. I...

05:08.800 --> 05:09.840
Chapter 3.

05:11.520 --> 05:12.720
Two Galota.

05:30.800 --> 05:36.000
Hazarfen doesn't fly. He falls.

05:37.680 --> 05:45.440
Mehmed hears a big crash and a cry from the foot of the hill.

05:47.920 --> 05:51.840
He goes quickly down the hill to his friend.

05:52.080 --> 06:00.720
Hazarfen is lying under his wings. Ali is next to him.

06:00.720 --> 06:05.600
His legs broken. Ali says.

06:05.600 --> 06:08.480
No, it isn't.

06:08.480 --> 06:11.440
Hazarfen answers.

06:11.440 --> 06:18.960
My wings are broken, but I'm okay. This time.

06:19.600 --> 06:25.600
Mehmed cries. But, what about next time?

06:25.600 --> 06:31.360
Be careful, my friend. You don't want to die.

06:32.720 --> 06:38.720
They take the broken wings back to Hazarfen's workshop.

06:41.120 --> 06:44.480
Now what? Ali asks.

06:45.280 --> 06:49.040
I understand more.

06:50.480 --> 06:54.560
The design of my wings needs to be different.

06:55.840 --> 07:01.120
Bigger and better. But that can wait.

07:02.080 --> 07:03.600
Hazarfen says.

07:04.880 --> 07:11.440
Right now, I must go and see the district chief of Galota.

07:12.240 --> 07:13.840
Galota?

07:13.840 --> 07:15.760
Mehmed cries.

07:15.760 --> 07:17.200
Why?

07:17.200 --> 07:26.080
I want to fly from the Galota tower, so I need his permission for that.

07:26.080 --> 07:28.240
Forget it.

07:28.240 --> 07:35.440
The district chief never asks people into his office.

07:35.440 --> 07:37.360
Ali says.

07:37.360 --> 07:39.600
Let's see.

07:40.480 --> 07:43.040
Hazarfen cries.

07:43.040 --> 07:45.040
Come on!

07:45.040 --> 07:51.760
And he and his friends take a boat across the Bosphorus.

07:55.200 --> 08:02.480
The three friends walk from the Bosphorus up to the Galota tower.

08:04.160 --> 08:08.800
Two tall guards stop them when they arrive.

08:10.400 --> 08:12.160
What do you want?

08:12.160 --> 08:13.520
One of them asks.

08:14.720 --> 08:18.880
We want to see the district chief of Galota.

08:20.160 --> 08:21.840
Hazarfen answers.

08:23.120 --> 08:26.160
Ali and Mehmed are afraid.

08:27.200 --> 08:28.560
What's your name?

08:29.760 --> 08:31.120
The guard asks.

08:32.480 --> 08:35.360
Hazarfen amed chilebi.

08:36.320 --> 08:41.520
Ah, the brother of the rocket maker.

08:41.520 --> 08:45.200
Lageri Hassan chilebi.

08:46.720 --> 08:50.160
All Istanbul is talking of him.

08:51.120 --> 08:52.320
The guard says.

08:53.920 --> 08:58.400
Yes, Hazarfen answers tiredly.

08:59.840 --> 09:03.600
So, can I see the district chief?

09:04.240 --> 09:06.240
He asks the man.

09:07.440 --> 09:08.240
Wait!

09:08.960 --> 09:10.400
The guard says.

09:11.760 --> 09:15.840
And he goes into the district chief's office.

09:15.840 --> 09:17.840
The guard says.

09:31.840 --> 09:32.800
Chapter 4.

09:34.320 --> 09:43.040
A brother's help.

09:45.840 --> 09:49.120
A brother's help.

09:54.400 --> 10:02.560
Sometime later, the guard takes Hazarfen to the district chief's office.

10:04.400 --> 10:08.320
Mehmed and Ali wait at the door.

10:08.560 --> 10:15.520
The district chief listens to Hazarfen's story.

10:17.600 --> 10:20.960
Very well, he smiles.

10:22.080 --> 10:25.040
You can fly from the tower.

10:26.560 --> 10:28.640
But be careful.

10:29.920 --> 10:32.640
Don't fall and die.

10:35.040 --> 10:37.120
No, district chief.

10:38.400 --> 10:40.080
Hazarfen answers.

10:41.760 --> 10:45.200
And I'd like to see your brother.

10:46.480 --> 10:47.280
Tell him.

10:48.560 --> 10:50.480
Yes, district chief.

10:51.520 --> 10:52.960
Hazarfen says.

10:57.520 --> 10:59.360
I got permission.

11:00.240 --> 11:04.800
Hazarfen laughs when he comes out into the street.

11:05.760 --> 11:06.400
Good!

11:07.120 --> 11:09.040
Ali cries happily.

11:10.080 --> 11:10.960
What now?

11:12.080 --> 11:13.520
Mehmed asks.

11:14.880 --> 11:16.960
I must visit Lageri.

11:18.000 --> 11:19.520
Hazarfen says.

11:22.960 --> 11:27.040
So, Hazarfen visits his older brother.

11:28.640 --> 11:32.000
Lageri is working on his rocket.

11:32.880 --> 11:34.880
When Hazarfen arrives.

11:37.120 --> 11:38.400
Nice design.

11:39.680 --> 11:41.280
Hazarfen says.

11:42.640 --> 11:45.280
Yes, Lageri answers.

11:46.160 --> 11:52.560
Perhaps early next year, I can fly up into the sky in it.

11:53.680 --> 11:54.640
What about you?

11:55.680 --> 11:56.880
Me, brother.

11:58.160 --> 12:01.440
I want to fly across the sky.

12:02.160 --> 12:05.520
With my wings later this year.

12:06.640 --> 12:10.080
So, it's a race.

12:11.120 --> 12:12.480
Lageri laughs.

12:13.600 --> 12:16.560
Yes, Hazarfen smiles.

12:17.760 --> 12:18.560
But listen.

12:19.840 --> 12:23.920
The district chief of Galata wants to see you.

12:24.960 --> 12:25.440
Right.

12:26.320 --> 12:28.960
Well, thank you for your visit.

12:29.920 --> 12:32.880
Good luck with your wings, Hazarfen.

12:34.080 --> 12:36.880
Good luck with your rocket, Lageri.

12:38.240 --> 12:40.640
And Hazarfen leaves.

12:44.320 --> 12:50.000
Two weeks later, Hazarfen's new wings are ready.

12:51.520 --> 12:56.000
Now I can fly from Galata to Uskudar.

12:57.040 --> 12:57.920
He cries.

12:59.440 --> 13:00.000
Wait!

13:01.040 --> 13:05.360
You must ask the Sultan's permission for that, I think.

13:06.240 --> 13:07.360
Mehmed says.

13:08.160 --> 13:14.560
And the Sultan says no to most people when they ask for things.

13:16.000 --> 13:18.000
So, what can I do?

13:19.040 --> 13:20.640
Hazarfen cries.

13:22.560 --> 13:23.040
Listen.

13:24.160 --> 13:28.400
These days, the district chief of Galata

13:29.120 --> 13:32.240
talks about your brother a lot.

13:33.680 --> 13:38.160
Now the Sultan's interested in him too.

13:39.760 --> 13:45.680
Perhaps Lageri can ask the Sultan for a meeting.

13:46.640 --> 13:47.680
Ali says.

13:49.760 --> 13:54.960
So, Hazarfen goes and speaks to his brother again.

13:55.200 --> 13:59.680
Yes, I can ask the Sultan.

13:59.680 --> 14:01.680
Lageri smiles.

14:01.680 --> 14:06.400
But, he can always say no to a meeting.

14:06.400 --> 14:07.120
To a meeting.

14:24.080 --> 14:25.040
Chapter 5

14:26.560 --> 14:28.640
What does the Sultan say?

14:36.400 --> 14:50.640
So, Lageri speaks to the Sultan.

14:51.680 --> 14:55.360
And the Sultan says yes to a meeting.

14:57.680 --> 15:02.880
Seven days later, Hazarfen goes to the palace.

15:03.120 --> 15:07.600
He walks past the higher Sophia.

15:09.120 --> 15:10.560
He is nervous.

15:12.000 --> 15:14.080
Please give me permission.

15:15.360 --> 15:16.080
He thinks.

15:18.160 --> 15:22.480
Near the blue mask, he is more nervous.

15:24.320 --> 15:26.000
Please say yes.

15:27.360 --> 15:28.080
He thinks.

15:28.080 --> 15:33.360
Hazarfen stops near the palace.

15:35.360 --> 15:38.800
The Sultan can, of course, say no.

15:40.320 --> 15:45.200
Or worse, he can say, kill that man.

15:46.480 --> 15:47.360
He thinks.

15:49.280 --> 15:52.480
I'm Hazarfen Ahmed Chelebi.

15:53.520 --> 15:55.760
The Sultan wants to see me.

15:56.560 --> 15:58.960
He tells the palace guard.

16:00.480 --> 16:02.000
The man goes in.

16:03.760 --> 16:05.440
Hazarfen waits.

16:06.800 --> 16:09.120
He is very nervous now.

16:11.760 --> 16:15.680
After an hour, the guard comes back.

16:16.800 --> 16:17.680
Come with me.

16:18.800 --> 16:20.720
He says to Hazarfen.

16:21.040 --> 16:29.360
Hazarfen bows very nervously when he meets the Sultan.

16:31.520 --> 16:32.480
Your Highness.

16:33.760 --> 16:37.680
I want to fly across the Bosporus.

16:38.720 --> 16:39.360
He says.

16:40.800 --> 16:42.880
The Sultan smiles.

16:44.240 --> 16:45.520
Ah, yes.

16:46.320 --> 16:52.240
Your Lagari Hassan's brother, he says.

16:54.160 --> 16:55.920
Yes, your Highness.

16:57.040 --> 16:58.640
Hazarfen answers.

17:00.480 --> 17:04.320
Then he asks for the Sultan's permission.

17:06.480 --> 17:07.840
You have it.

17:09.200 --> 17:10.320
The Sultan says.

17:10.400 --> 17:16.480
You must fly across the Bosporus tomorrow.

17:18.880 --> 17:22.720
With a good wind, Hazarfen says.

17:23.920 --> 17:28.480
But without it, what then your Highness?

17:30.000 --> 17:33.600
You must ask God for a wind.

17:34.720 --> 17:36.240
The Sultan smiles.

17:37.920 --> 17:39.120
Your Highness.

17:40.400 --> 17:42.400
A vizier says quietly.

17:44.000 --> 17:46.720
People can walk with their legs.

17:47.680 --> 17:50.240
But we don't have wings.

17:51.600 --> 17:56.080
Is a flying man good in God's eyes?

17:58.480 --> 17:58.960
Listen.

18:00.240 --> 18:01.520
The Sultan answers.

18:03.040 --> 18:06.640
We can think of new things with our brains.

18:07.600 --> 18:10.080
And our brains come from God.

18:11.280 --> 18:16.720
The first flying man must be an Ottoman, I say.

18:17.920 --> 18:19.840
Yes, your Highness.

18:20.960 --> 18:22.160
The vizier says.

18:23.600 --> 18:27.120
But he looks angrily at Hazarfen.

18:29.520 --> 18:33.520
That evening, Hazarfen is not happy.

18:34.320 --> 18:36.800
There's no wind.

18:37.840 --> 18:40.160
He tells Mehmed and Ali.

18:55.600 --> 19:00.000
Chapter 6 Hazarfen's Reward

19:04.400 --> 19:22.960
The next morning, there is lots of wind.

19:24.800 --> 19:32.160
Hazarfen stands happily with his wings at the top of the Galota tower.

19:34.080 --> 19:36.480
Suddenly, he jumps.

19:37.680 --> 19:39.360
He's falling!

19:40.640 --> 19:41.600
People cry.

19:43.120 --> 19:45.440
But he is not falling.

19:46.960 --> 19:56.320
He is flying with his big white wings over the houses of Galota.

19:58.400 --> 20:02.720
Hazarfen's friends Mehmed and Ali.

20:03.680 --> 20:08.480
Run with the people down the streets to the Bosphorus.

20:10.160 --> 20:14.400
Hazarfen flies out over the water.

20:16.080 --> 20:18.000
I'm flying!

20:19.600 --> 20:20.560
He cries.

20:21.680 --> 20:24.320
People can fly!

20:25.920 --> 20:31.280
He lands across the street in Ushkudar, a happy man.

20:34.400 --> 20:40.960
The next day, the Sultan has a meeting with his viziers at the palace.

20:41.840 --> 20:44.320
People can fly!

20:45.760 --> 20:47.920
He cries excitedly.

20:48.880 --> 20:54.320
And the first flying man is an Ottoman.

20:55.600 --> 20:58.720
That's good for our empire.

21:00.000 --> 21:02.800
Hazarfen is a good man.

21:03.520 --> 21:06.560
Hazarfen needs a reward.

21:08.160 --> 21:10.160
But your highness.

21:10.720 --> 21:13.440
The vizier, nearest to him, says.

21:14.480 --> 21:20.560
Flying men can land in our palaces and kill us.

21:21.760 --> 21:23.600
They're dangerous.

21:26.320 --> 21:28.960
The Sultan thinks about this.

21:28.960 --> 21:34.800
Yes, I see.

21:36.080 --> 21:38.000
Perhaps you're right.

21:39.200 --> 21:44.320
So, what must we do with Hazarfen then?

21:45.600 --> 21:46.400
He asks.

21:48.160 --> 21:51.760
Kill him, the vizier answers.

21:53.680 --> 21:55.920
I can't do that.

21:55.920 --> 21:58.720
But the Sultan cries.

22:00.080 --> 22:02.720
Then, exile him.

22:03.920 --> 22:05.200
The vizier says.

22:09.360 --> 22:16.080
So, the Sultan calls Hazarfen Ahmed Chilebi to the palace.

22:17.840 --> 22:22.800
He gives a reward of a thousand gold coins to him.

22:22.960 --> 22:28.480
Then, he exiles him to Algeria.

22:30.880 --> 22:37.120
Hazarfen says goodbye to his brother and his friends.

22:38.960 --> 22:42.400
He leaves Istanbul that evening.

22:44.080 --> 22:52.240
After that, he can fly over the Bosphorus with the birds in his dreams.

22:53.520 --> 22:58.800
But he can never go back to Istanbul again.

23:01.040 --> 23:04.560
And what about Legari and his rocket?

23:05.200 --> 23:05.920
You ask.

23:07.440 --> 23:13.760
Well, perhaps one day I can tell you that story too.

